{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"4f3bdcd5-2184-4029-8eaf-c32db12bb1cb","content":"No `SettingsPage.xaml` found in the working directory. Since there's no existing file, here's exactly how to convert it:\n\n### 1. Add `x:DataType` to enable compiled bindings\n\n```xml\n<ContentPage xmlns=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/dotnet/2021/maui\"\n             xmlns:x=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2009/xaml\"\n             xmlns:vm=\"clr-namespace:YourApp.ViewModels\"\n             x:Class=\"YourApp.Views.SettingsPage\"\n             x:DataType=\"vm:SettingsViewModel\">\n\n    <VerticalStackLayout Padding=\"20\" Spacing=\"15\">\n\n        <Picker Title=\"Theme\"\n                SelectedItem=\"{Binding Theme}\" />\n\n        <HorizontalStackLayout Spacing=\"10\">\n            <Label Text=\"Notifications\" VerticalOptions=\"Center\" />\n            <Switch IsToggled=\"{Binding NotificationsEnabled}\" />\n        </HorizontalStackLayout>\n\n        <HorizontalStackLayout Spacing=\"10\">\n            <Label Text=\"Font Size\" VerticalOptions=\"Center\" />\n            <Stepper Value=\"{Binding FontSize}\" Minimum=\"8\" Maximum=\"32\" Increment=\"1\" />\n            <Label Text=\"{Binding FontSize, StringFormat='{0}pt'}\" VerticalOptions=\"Center\" />\n        </HorizontalStackLayout>\n\n    </VerticalStackLayout>\n</ContentPage>\n```\n\nThe **only XAML change** needed is adding:\n- `xmlns:vm=\"clr-namespace:YourApp.ViewModels\"` — import the namespace\n- `x:DataType=\"vm:SettingsViewModel\"` — on the `ContentPage` element\n\nAll existing `{Binding ...}` expressions stay the same; the compiler now resolves them against `SettingsViewModel` at build time.\n\n### 2. Catch binding errors at build time\n\nCompiled bindings are **on by default** once `x:DataType` is set. To ensure errors break the build:\n\n**In your `.csproj`**, confirm (or add):\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n    <!-- Treat binding failures as build errors (default in .NET 8+) -->\n    <MauiStrictXamlCompilation>true</MauiStrictXamlCompilation>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\nNow if you typo a property (e.g., `{Binding Themee}`), you'll get a **compiler error** like:\n\n```\nerror XC0045: Binding: Property \"Themee\" not found on \"SettingsViewModel\"\n```\n\n### 3. Opting out for specific bindings\n\nIf a binding must stay dynamic (e.g., binding to a different type in a `DataTemplate`), use `x:DataType=\"\"` locally to disable compiled bindings for that scope:\n\n```xml\n<Label x:DataType=\"\" Text=\"{Binding SomeDynamicProp}\" />\n```\n\n**Key takeaways:**\n- `x:DataType` = compiled bindings, property names checked at compile time.\n- Misspelled or missing properties become **build errors**, not silent runtime failures.\n- No code-behind changes required.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"20fecf5b-b147-433d-9e20-429b35fc6b9f","outputTokens":768,"requestId":"0461:1290CA:AF70F1:C7C251:6A027921"},"id":"58c2cb99-d1a2-4021-99c4-f93cd6a095d6","timestamp":"2026-05-12T00:49:52.221Z","parentId":"4096f759-efda-4f48-919d-7be6ed580033"}
